<h3>Course Goals</h3>

The primary goal of the course is <b>mathematical intellectual
  growth</b>. This involves understanding mathematical concepts,
  analysis and problem solving, and clear, concise communication.
  Achievement of course goals requires desire for learning, willingness
  to work hard, time (at least two hours on homework outside of
  class for each hour in class), and persistence. Student learning objectives 
  include the following.
<ul>
<li><b>understanding of mathematical concepts</b>
<li><b>analysis and problem solving skills</b> 
<li><b>clear, concise communication skills</b>
<li><b>mastery of the course material</b> at a satisfactory
  level (grade `C') or higher
</ul>


<h3>Course Calendar</h3>

The calendar for reading assignments, exercises, class discussions,
and exams is posted on Canvas. The calendar is subject to change.


